    <h4>Order Workflow States</h4>
    <p>Orders have one of several workflow states and available actions to support the acquisitions workflow.</p>
  <p>For administrators, each status has a list of available actions to change status.</p>

    <table class="table table-striped table-bordered">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>State</th>
          <th>Available Actions</th>
          <th>Notes</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
         <tr>
        <td>Provisional</td>
        <td>Approve, Reject</td>
        <td>Tricerashopper includes <i>Assistant</i> accounts that are authorized to create provisional materials reqeusts for review by selectors. Assistant requests are entered with a <i>Provisional</i> workflow state, Selectors must select Approve (-> New), or, Reject (-> Rejected) actions to move the order forward.</td>
      </tr>
        <tr>
        <td>New</td>
        <td>Marc yes po, Marc no po, Ordered, Reject, Temporary hold</td>
        <td>New is the default status for incoming orders submitted by selectors.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Marc yes po</td>
        <td>Marc no po, Ordered, Temporary hold</td>
        <td>Orders with this status are queued for batch MARC record generation, records will print a PO when loaded into Sierra.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Marc no po</td>
